brewery.brewery_description:
The Swedish word “väsen” honors our Scandinavian heritage and translates as one’s inner essence or way of being. At Väsen Brewing Company, brewing is about creating and appreciating something greater than yourself. Our beer is a medium through which we express ourselves and our appreciation for our environment. We brew to inspire others to chase the things they love.

Väsen beers combine the experimental spirit that defines American craft beer with the rustic and funky flavors of Belgian farmhouse and sour ales.

We’ve developed a distinctive brewing process that produces balanced, sessionable beers that are perfect for long days outside. While our barrel-aging program will let us flood Richmond with the funkiest of farmhouse ales, they’ll be complemented by a variety of Saisons, wheat beers, and pale ales.

Our goal is to make unconventional ales and celebrate those who share an appreciation for the outdoors and spark positive change in their communities.

beer.beer_description: This Abbey-style ale was aged with grapefruit for 4 months in Chardonnay barrels to impart intense flavors of citrus, oak, and vanilla. A generous addition of Nelson Sauvin hops from New Zealand provides subtle fruitiness and enhances the white wine character of this strong, bold brew. Hints of cherry, clove, and black pepper lead into a surprisingly smooth finish.

beer.beer_description: This crisp, fruity, sour spent weeks on hundreds of pounds of blood peaches, giving it a warm rosy hue. An initial hit of ripe fruit is followed by subtle smokiness and a hint of toffee.

The APS is a true Väsen original. Our version of an IPA is a double dry-hopped golden saison with moderate bitterness that is balanced by its full body and smooth finish. Flavors and aromas of ripe peaches and grapefruit from Citra hops meld with freshly baked bread and subtle nuttiness contributed by Maris Otter malt from the U.K.
Tropical. Salty. Sour. Delicious.
Medium brown in hue, our dubbel offers a sweetly nutty aroma as well as chocolate and toasty flavors that give way to a smooth dry finish.
A refreshing medium-bodied saison with passion fruit added for tropical flavor and aroma
A strong golden-colored ale with high carbonation and a balanced smoked malt aroma and flavor

Time to float! Everything Floats on Soursop is the newest version of our dry-hopped, moderately sour take on a hazy New England IPA. Soursop, a fruit native to South America, contributes bright tropical flavors reminiscent of grapefruit, pineapple, and strawberry. This fragrant, hoppy brew was generously dry-hopped with Vic Secret hops from Australia and Mandarina Bavaria hops from Germany to produce a complex, lightly bitter sour perfect for the beginning of spring.

This triple-dry-hopped pale ale was conditioned on Ekuanot, Amarillo, and Galaxy hops to produce a complex, well-rounded hop character with hints of grapefruit, tangerine, and pine. Traditional Norwegian kveik yeast from a farm in northern Norway contribute complex aromas of orange peel, peach, and white pepper, which combine with rich brown sugar and honey to balance this moderately bitter farmhouse-style ale.

Spring is here and the beast has awoken from hibernation! The biggest of our abbey-style ales, the sugarbear is smooth, dark, and more than a little dangerous. Maple, dark chocolate, and vanilla dominate this malty brew, but those who dare to challenge this bear will be rewarded with notes of clove and toffee with subtle apricot and cherry. Careful, it's ferocious!

We all float down there. Yes we do! The third version of our juicy triple-dry-hopped sour was conditioned on nearly half a ton of passionfruit and generous additions of Vic Secret, Mandarina Bavaria, and Citra hops. Passionfruit dominates this big, hazy beast, but grapefruit, pineapple, and tangerine lurk beneath its sour surface.

Our most sour beer yet, this dark, aggressively tart ale was conditioned on Morello sour cherries to give it wine-like richness and depth. Bold tangerine, strawberry and cherry flavors meld with understated notes of chocolate, toffee, and toast from lightly roasted European malts, which lead to a smooth, dry finish.
A lightly sour saison that pops with notes of bright citrus, rounded out by a smooth malty finish

The name says it all. Dark stone fruit and roasted malt aromas draw you into what feels familiar, but you know something is different about this beer. A surge of rich, stouty tartness washes over your tongue, smashing all preconceptions, and vanishes just as quickly, leaving only a lingering crisp maltiness in its wake.
The final stout in the Walrus Series spent three months in whiskey barrels, imparting vanilla, oak and toffee. Smooth dark chocolate and ripe cherries round out this extremely drinkable winter beer.
This effervescent sour ale, brewed with tangerine peels, starts with a refreshing citrus tartness that leads to a medium malty finish.
This pale gold color crusher offers hints of banana and berry flavor and aromatics balanced by hay and malt notes that come together in a superbly dry finish

Dried hibiscus petals give this extremely tart brew a gorgeous red tint and add notes of cranberry, cherry, and freshly cut flowers, as well as a subtle earthiness. Our house Lacto mother and traditional German ale yeast have combined to make a surprisingly funky sour beer with a light, clean finish that is perfect for brisk spring afternoons on the patio.
Artfully blending tart and savory, this hazy golden beer quenches like no others and bursts with juicy citrus followed by pleasantly salty finish

Saison with fig. The third release celebrating Saison Month was conditioned on French fig puree to create a slightly spicy saison with hints of black pepper, clove, and honey. This earthy, red-gold ale has a dry, refreshing finish perfect for a spring afternoon in Scott’s Addition.
This rich, bold stout is cold-steeped with fair-trade, single-origin Guatemalan coffee beans from Blanchard's to create a smooth blend of mocha, chamomile, and dried plums.

Bright and complex citrus aromas leap from this light, hazy sour thanks to hundreds of pounds of tangerines, tangerine peel, and Citra hops. Light notes of strawberry, apricot and honey provide complexity to this fruity tangerine bomb.

There can be only one beer like this one! This big, Trappist-style ale is brewed with peated malt from the United Kingdom for a restrained smokey character. East Kent Golding and Hallertau hops contribute gentle floral and spicy aromas, while a traditional Belgian Trappist yeast strain imparts a wide range of subtle fruit flavors, including melon, stone-fruit, and citrus.

Hops from three continents make this fruity beer a real globetrotter! Crisp and sour, yet smooth, this slightly bitter beer is extremely hoppy with bold notes of pineapple, grapefruit, guava and passion fruit.

Saison with peach. The fourth and final release celebrating Saison Month is a fruity, but refreshingly dry saison conditioned on white peach. Bright flavors of ripe peach, strawberry, and papaya lead to a balanced finish just dry enough to lead you into the next sip.
Waves of velvety chocolate ganache and ripe red raspberries lead into a pleasantly smooth and mildly roasty finish.
